            <title>TikTok 疯传 Apple Watch 戴落脚，用家在健身房被误会戴电子脚镣</title>
            <link>https://unwire.hk/2025/02/11/apple-watch-ankle-trend/life-tech/watch-wireless-home/?utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=apple-watch-ankle-trend</link>
            <comments>https://unwire.hk/2025/02/11/apple-watch-ankle-trend/life-tech/watch-wireless-home/#respond</comments>
            <dc:creator>
                <![CDATA[Oscar]]>
            </dc:creator>
            <pubDate>Tue, 11 Feb 2025 09:26:28 +0000</pubDate>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[潮流手表]]>
            </category>
            <category>
                <![CDATA[apple watch]]>
            </category>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://unwire.hk/?p=1291079</guid>
            <description>
                <![CDATA[<p>无论你习惯将手表佩戴在左手还是右手，相信一般人都会将手表戴在手腕上。不过近日 TikTok 上有 KOL 带动一股新热潮，建议用家不要将  Apple Watch 戴在手腕上，反而推荐用家佩戴在脚踝上，表示这种佩戴方式收集到的运动数据更加准确。然而这种新作法屡屡引发误解，甚至让部分佩戴者被误认为正在接受电子监管。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1291120" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/anklewatchseries9v0h-425x580.jpeg" alt="" width="425" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/anklewatchseries9v0h-425x580.jpeg 425w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/anklewatchseries9v0h.jpeg 660w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 425px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/AppleWatch/comments/1d62fi7/ankle_watch_series9/">Reddit</a></p><p>《纽约时报》报道指，健身 KOL Ana Espinal 表示，由于自己手腕较纤细，感应器无法贴合皮肤，佩戴 Apple Watch 时心率监测不稳定，导致健身应用程式纪录时常中断。最后 Ana Espinal 尝试将 Apple Watch 绑于脚踝后，发现问题迎刃而解。Ana Espinal 随后在 TikTok 分享这个小技巧，引来不少用户仿效。</p><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1291122" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/morepeoplearenowwear-580x580.jpeg" alt="" width="580" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/morepeoplearenowwear-580x580.jpeg 580w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/morepeoplearenowwear-144x144.jpeg 144w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/morepeoplearenowwear.jpeg 640w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 580px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/AppleWatch/comments/1im7vgy/more_people_are_now_wearing_apple_watch_on_their/">Reddit</a></p><p>《纽约时报》综合了 5 个用家选择将 Apple Watch 戴在脚上的原因：</p><ul><li>部分用家认为自己手腕过幼，Apple Watch 感应器无法贴近皮肤；</li><li>手腕有纹身的用家认为墨水会干扰心率感应；</li><li>有人认为戴在脚踝上可以收集更准确的步数；</li><li>部分用家手部皮肤较敏感，佩戴在脚踝上较为舒适；</li><li>有些医疗专业人员不得在手腕佩戴任何东西。</li></ul><p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1291125" src="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2025021134235-352x580.jpg" alt="" width="352" height="580" srcset="https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2025021134235-352x580.jpg 352w, https://cdn.unwire.hk/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/2025021134235.jpg 546w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 639px) 98vw, (max-width: 1199px) 64vw, 352px" /></p><p style="text-align: center;">▲图片来源：<a href="https://www.tiktok.com/discover/wearing-apple-watch-on-ankle-no-ankle-strap">TikTok</a></p><p>由于脚踝佩戴智能手表方式较罕见，不少使用者在公众场合时常被误解。Ana Espinal 表示，曾经试过在健身房被误会正在佩戴电子脚镣，她只好解释自己只是想获取更准确的健身数据。至于曾醉酒驾驶被判处佩戴电子脚镣的演员 Jason Rogers 则无法接受这股潮流。他直言：「经历两年电子脚镣后，绝对不可能再戴任何东西在脚踝上！」</p><p>图片、资料来源：<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2025/02/08/style/apple-watch-ankles.html">New York Times</a>、<a href="https://techcrunch.com/2025/02/10/tiktok-influencers-are-wearing-apple-watches-on-their-ankles/">Tech Cruch</a>、<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/02/10/wearing-apple-watch-on-ankle/">Mac Rumors</a></p><p>======</p><p>加入 <a href="https://www.threads.net/@unwirehk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">unwire thread</a> 倾倾科技背后黑暗事</p><p>========</p><br /><b>
]]>
            </description>
            <wfw:commentRss>https://unwire.hk/2025/02/11/apple-watch-ankle-trend/life-tech/watch-wireless-home/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
